SENATE JOINT RESOLUTION 719
By Yarbro
A RESOLUTION to congratulate Maggie Crosslin of St. Cecilia
Academy on winning the 2025 TSSAA Division
II, Class A Girls' Cross Country Individual
Championship.
WHEREAS, the members of this General Assembly are pleased to specially honor and
commend those successful high school athletes who, through their magnificent exploits, bring
honor to Tennessee and serve as exceptional ambassadors of this State; and
WHEREAS, one such estimable athlete is Maggie Crosslin of St. Cecilia Academy, who
won the 2025 TSSAA Division II, Class A Girls' Individual State Cross Country Championship
held at Shelby Farms Park in Memphis on November 6, 2025; and
WHEREAS, Ms. Crosslin's time of 18:34 put her nearly thirty seconds ahead of her
closest competitor from Grace Christian Academy in Knoxville; and
WHEREAS, earlier this year, Maggie Crosslin placed third in the TSSAA State Track and
Field 800m at 2:17 and was named to the Tennessee Sports Writers Association DII-AA All-
State Track and Field Team; her performance earned her an invitation to the New Balance
Nationals in Philadelphia, Pennsylvania, in June, where she competed in the Girls
Championship 2000m Steeplechase; and
WHEREAS, she is an all-around St. Cecilia student, taking five AP classes this
semester, while also serving as captain of the cross country team, president of the National
Honor Society, and as a student council representative; and
WHEREAS, Ms. Crosslin's noteworthy achievement is a tremendous source of pride for
her family, her school, and her community; and
WHEREAS, Maggie Crosslin's dedication to excellence is clearly deserving of our
respect, admiration, and commendation; now, therefore,
SJR0719
013030
- 1 -

BE IT RESOLVED BY THE SENATE OF THE ONE HUNDRED FOURTEENTH
GENERAL ASSEMBLY OF THE STATE OF TENNESSEE, THE HOUSE OF
REPRESENTATIVES CONCURRING, that we honor and congratulate Maggie Crosslin of St.
Cecilia Academy on winning the 2025 TSSAA Division II, Class A Girls' Cross Country Individual
Championship and extend to her our best wishes for much continued success in her future
endeavors.
BE IT FURTHER RESOLVED, that an appropriate copy of this resolution be prepared
for presentation with this final clause omitted from such copy and upon proper request made to
the appropriate clerk, the language appearing immediately following the State seal appear
without House or Senate designation.
